# CleanMateX Order Financial Migration

Before editing order/payment/financial code, read:

```text
/architecture-docs/order-financial-migration
```

## Critical Rules

- Do not rewrite checkout.
- Do not break preview-payment.
- Do not break create-with-payment.
- Do not remove AMOUNT_MISMATCH.
- Do not remove legacy fields during migration.
- Use expand → dual-write → reconcile → switch-read → retire.
- Gift card is liability, not discount.
- Wallet/customer credit/advance are stored-value applications, not payments.
- Invoice is AR, not payment.
- Preferences are operational selections.
- Charges are monetary additions.
- Tax happens before credits/payments.
- One payment row per real payment leg.
- One credit application row per stored-value usage.
- Every tenant-owned table/query must include tenant_org_id.
